content: Absolutely useless. When I open the app and tap on the + button to hide the software update notification it says I don't have any notifications. Great! So now I'm stuck with this annoying notification that won't go away. Galaxy S10 user.

It used to work... Used it for a good 2 or 3 months on my tablet, then suddenly I turned it on and the notification is back, and this app doesn't pick it up anymore. I have an LTE Tab S6 with no SIM card, so I was using this to hide the annoying prompt to insert one.
After an update for my Samsung Galaxy Note 10 Plus, this app stopped working. It doesn't hide notifications anymore.
I'm not convinced it's doing anything...it shows its hiding notifications for apps I don't even have and I keep seeing some apps coming through again
Neat, simple, works. Tested on Android 10 on Sony Xperia 1II to disable the system software update notification
Does not work

Completely useless. The app does absolutely nothing to prevent notifications on my Samsung Galaxy S20 even after I selected the 'Software Update' notification to be hidden.
Claims to have a 48 hour return policy, rejects refund requests within that time period. Straight up liars
Great app, thanks :)
No longer hides the Samsung configuration update notification.

Thank goodness for this application! I got real tired of this forced update notification that Samsung had put on my phone for months now and this program put an end to the headache of seeing it. It's my phone so it's my choice when and if I update it, that's what Samsung and Google both fail to realize. Thank you to whom made this app!
Does exactly what I want it too.
Note 20 Ultra - Android 11 - works beautifully. Thank you

Bloody Android. I've turned off updates, auto updates and turned update off in Developer Options. They screw things up and take useful options away. But the swines still force the notification that there's an update available. They've no right. It's my choice. Once upon a time turning updates off stopped all update related features, not any more, they nag, nag, nag. Now the damn notification has gone, I hope it'll keep it gone, even when Android tries to force it back with the next update.

Easy and it's working for me! Got rid of that nagging Samsung update which is great because their latest update on the S10 stole my hotspot functionality! Now I'm using an older phone because they sabotaged me again. Very much appreciate this tiny app.
Fixed my "software update" notification problem within 10 seconds. Truly worth it!

Waste of money. Didnt want the most recent update on my phone and this morning I wake up to a notification that the update has been installed. I'll update to two stars if I can get a refund but that's all it'd be worth. Just skip this junk.
Not work at all
I bought this app to disable the lock screen sim card network name notifications on an s20+. How can I do this? Edit: so, no response from the dev and no chance of a refund. Thanks everyone ðŸ˜”
Wish it was free but definitely does its job.
Works great... When it works. Drops out all the time unfortunately. Shame. Used to be good.
Works for Android 10
Does exactly what it says it's gonna do. Very easy to use.
Works like a charm. Android 10 on S20, tablet.
Not compatible with Android 10. When I used it on Android 9. It was perfect!

$3 is steep, but this app delivers the goods AND the dev has been very considerate with the UI and overall design. Shouldn't need an indie dev to fix Google's idiotic permission mistakes but Google doesn't make good decisions anymore.
Stops hiding notifications randomly.
Jesus christ it actually works. Note 10+ running latest Android (non-root) 150% worth the dough.
Looked promising but the fossil hybrid sync app reappeares a few minutes after being hidden.
Does what it says on the tin

Buy this app, it's perfect! It makes you decide which notifications you want get ride off and which doesn't. I don't know how is this app not more popular, but I loved it. Finally I can have the notifications I really need in my status bar. Thanks a lot!
Fixed my annoying persistent notification problem within 60 seconds of opening the app. :)

Amazing app, works almost flawlessly except that when my phone is on vibrate, it will vibrate every 5 second or so (which sucks because I always use vibrate). Luckily this doesn't happen when it's on full alert so it's still worth the trouble of dealing with notification sounds I guess
this is great! downloaded a dns changer that had a system locked perma-notification. a must have!

completely drained my battery. I had to uninstall the app
It's brilliant! Works perfectly. I used it for do not disturb on Samsung

Allows me to hide persistent notifications and keep the benefits of having a persistent notification. Unlike disabling a notification in my phones settings. This is particularly helpful with IFTTT and its very useful but annoying persistent notification.
The only app that allowed me to remove the "do not disturb mode" persistent notification with one click, no root required, no adb permissions required. Worth every penny.
Excellent simple app to remove annoying persistent notifications like Wi-Fi calling and WhatsApp Web
One of the best apps on the play store, works flawlessly to finally hide all the incredibly annoying notifications I had persistently taking up space.
Essential app for anyone wanting a cleaner UI
This is the app I've been looking for. It works very well. Thank you.

This is a pretty essential app for hiding unnecessary notifications that otherwise cannot easily be turned off without heavy mod's, rooting, etc. I'm actually very surprised the lack of reviews for this app. Simple, does the job and works well. Working on my unlocked Samsung S8+ w/ Oreo v8.0. One minor issue I had was that after several weeks I had to blow out the app data and start over as it stopped being able to detect new notifications to block. But I don't really blame the app, I did a lot of tweaks, mods, and overlay installs and uninstalls since I installed this app. I'm not surprised it got confused. I would be confused for sure! Kudo's to the dev for a job well done.
